{{Wireless embedded system |brand=TRENDnet |model=TEW-821DAP |revision=V2.0R |fcc_date=08/31/2018 |manuf_country=China |manuf=Cameo |is_manuf=No |type=access point, bridge, repeater |fcc_id=XU8TEW821DAPV2 |ic_id=6337A-TEW821DAPV2 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=1 |pwr_poe=af |cpu1_brand=Qualcomm Atheros |cpu1_model=QCA9563 |cpu1_cspeed=750 |fla1_brand=Macronix |ram1_brand=Winbond |wi1_chip1_brand=Qualcomm Atheros |wi1_chip1_model=QCA9563 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |wi2_chip1_brand=Qualcomm Atheros |wi2_chip1_model=QCA9886 |wi2_802dot11_protocols=an+ac |wi2_txchains=2 |wi2_rxchains=2 |wi2_sstreams=2 |eth_chip1_brand=Atheros |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=1 |flags=Wave2, MU-MIMO, IP30, |802dot11_protocols=abgn+ac |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin }} {{TagLine|AC1200 Dual Band PoE Indoor Wireless Access Point}} :{{SupportPage|vendor=TRENDnet|prod=110_TEW-821DAP}}
Chip IDs are not legible in the FCC internal photos but the CPU is probably something like a [[Qualcomm Atheros]] QCA9563 since it appears to be 3x3 and ethernet is provided by a separate Atheros chip. The 5GHz radio is probably a QCA9886 since MU-MIMO support is claimed.
A third tx/rx chain from the CPU is present but unpopulated so another model could be built with 3x3:3 bgn support.
Lead-free logo and revision text consistent with Cameo manufacture is found on the PCB visible in the FCC EUT's photos. They're the presumed manufacturer.
* Web GUI: http://tew-821dap
